# RAG Engine System

The RAG Engine is the truth layer of LexMastery AI.

It ensures AI responses are grounded in real course content.

---

# Product Vision

RAG must:

- retrieve relevant learning content
- prevent hallucinations
- ground AI Tutor responses
- improve legal accuracy
- enforce citation-based reasoning

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

RAGController (Riverpod)

↓

RAGState

↓

Retriever Service

↓

Vector Database + Document Store

↓

Ranking Engine

---

# State Management

RAGState includes:

- loading
- retrieved
- merged
- error

Core Data:

- retrievedChunks
- embeddings
- sourceReferences
- rankedResults

---

# Retrieval Strategy

Hybrid retrieval:

1. Semantic vector search
2. Keyword fallback search
3. Metadata filtering
4. AI ranking layer

---

# Knowledge Sources

RAG pulls from:

- Courses
- Lessons
- Notes
- AI Tutor memory
- Bookmarked content

---

# Grounding Rules

AI must:

- always cite retrieved content when applicable
- never invent legal rules
- prefer course material over external knowledge
- clearly separate inference vs fact

---

# Context Injection

RAG injects:

- relevant lesson snippets
- course definitions
- prior user interactions
- jurisdiction context

---

# Ranking System

Results ranked by:

- semantic similarity
- user progress relevance
- recency of access
- difficulty alignment

---

# Offline Behaviour

- cached embeddings available
- limited retrieval offline
- no vector search offline

---

# API Contracts

POST /rag/query

POST /rag/feedback

GET /rag/history

---

# Analytics Events

rag_query

rag_result_retrieved

rag_used_in_ai_response

rag_cache_hit

---

# Performance

- retrieval <300ms target
- ranked results streamed progressively

---

# Error Handling

- fallback to cached results
- degrade gracefully to keyword search

---

# UX Rules

- RAG is invisible to user
- only reflected in AI Tutor responses
- never exposed directly in UI

---

# Accessibility

Must ensure:

- readable AI citations
- structured explanation output

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Retrieval logic

Ranking system

Embedding pipeline

Integration Tests:

AI Tutor + RAG flow

Offline fallback behavior

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating RAG features:

- always prioritize course content
- always enforce grounding rules
- always prevent hallucination
- never expose raw embeddings to UI